What is exception handling and what problem does it solve?

-- Answer:

Exception handling is a process that deals with errors that may occur within a 
a program that interacts with the outside world in a managable and predictable 
way. It solves the problem of a program being hung, destroyed, or stuck in a
continuous loop by allowing a "reserve" block of code to be ran shall an error 
occur, allowing an essential by-pass of the program malfunction. 